FBIS3-11661 "drlat057_b_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Pope Meets With Visiting Haitian Bishops FL2303125494 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 GMT 18 Mar FL2303125494 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] On Friday, 18 March, Pope John Paul II renewed the call for dialogue with all the components of Haitian society that he had issued on 15 January. It is up to the Haitians, he stated in a speech to the Haitian bishops who came to Rome on their quinquennial visit, to build their future based on the principles about which you have reminded them recently. The pope mentioned in his speech Haiti's numerous problems to which are added, he said, the obsessive problems created by the political instability and the economic embargo and most of all the shattering show of a nation in distress which is struggling day after day in order to survive. [passage omitted]
